#DESCRIPTION
#  Find local maximum and minimum of a cubic polynomial
#ENDDESCRIPTION
## Author('Utah ww group')
## Institution('Univeristy of Utah')
## DBsubject('Calculus')
## DBchapter('Applications of Differentiation')
## DBsection('Summary of Curve Sketching')
## AuthorText1('Dale Varberg, Edwin J. Purcell, and Steven E. Rigdon')
## TitleText1('Calculus')
## EditionText1('9')
## Section1('Applications of the Derivative')
## Problem1('')
## KEYWORDS('calculus')

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(1,5,1);
$b1 = random(6,10,1);
$coef3 = 2;
$coef2 = 3*($a1+$b1);
$coef1 = 6*$a1*$b1;
$coef0 = random(1,11,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The function \( f(x) = $coef3 x^3 - $coef2 x^2 + $coef1 x + $coef0 \)
has one local minimum and one local maximum. $BR
It is helpful to make a rough sketch of the graph to see what is happening. $BR
This function has a local minimum at \( x = \)  \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $b1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
with value \(f(x) = \) \{ans_rule(20) \}, $BR
EOT
$ans = $coef3*$b1**3 - $coef2*$b1**2 + $coef1*$b1 + $coef0;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and a local maximum at \( x = \)  \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $a1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
with value  \(f(x) = \) \{ans_rule(20) \}.
EOT
$ans = $coef3*$a1**3 - $coef2*$a1**2 + $coef1*$a1 + $coef0;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
